In QuickNetCore/Controllers/AMCStatusController.cs, GetAmcStatus(): split the single server-side query into (1) a scalar-only IQueryable that is searched/sorted/paged server-side, then (2) materialize and attach the Depts/Desgn collections client-side via bulk lookups, preserving the exact JSON shape { AmcStatusId, StatusName, UserName, Depts:[{DeptName}], Desgn:[{DesgnName}] }.

Replace the `var v = (...)` block (lines 59-80) with a scalar-only projection:

    var v = (from a in db.AmcStatuss
             join b in db.Users on a.CreatedBy equals b.Id
             select new
             {
                 a.AmcStatusId,
                 a.StatusName,
                 b.UserName,
             });

Keep the search (line 86) and sort (line 90-93) blocks unchanged (they only reference StatusName/scalar columns) and keep `recordsTotal = v.Count();` (line 95). Then replace line 96-97 with materialize-then-attach:

    var page = v.Skip(skip).Take(pageSize).ToList();
    var ids = page.Select(r => r.AmcStatusId).ToList();

    // bulk lookups (two round-trips total, mirrors EF6 per-row result but batched)
    var deptLk = (from z in db.AmcStatusDepts
                  join y in db.Departments on z.DeptId equals y.DepartmentID
                  where ids.Contains(z.AmcStatusId)
                  select new { z.AmcStatusId, DeptName = y.DepartmentName ?? "" })
                 .ToList()
                 .ToLookup(x => x.AmcStatusId);

    var desgLk = (from z in db.AmcStatusDesgs
                  join y in db.Designations on z.DesgId equals y.DesignationID
                  where ids.Contains(z.AmcStatusId)
                  select new { z.AmcStatusId, DesgnName = y.DesignationName ?? "" })
                 .ToList()
                 .ToLookup(x => x.AmcStatusId);

    var data = page.Select(r => new
    {
        r.AmcStatusId,
        r.StatusName,
        r.UserName,
        Depts = deptLk[r.AmcStatusId].Select(x => new { x.DeptName }).ToList(),
        Desgn = desgLk[r.AmcStatusId].Select(x => new { x.DesgnName }).ToList(),
    }).ToList();

    return Json(new { draw = draw, recordsFiltered = recordsTotal, recordsTotal = recordsTotal, data = data });

This is output-identical to legacy EF6 (same per-row Depts/Desgn lists, same nullâ†’"" coalescing) but uses three translatable queries instead of an untranslatable nested-collection projection. Note: the bulk-lookup join filters out orphaned rows whose Department/Designation FK is missing â€” identical to the legacy inner-join behavior. If exact paging count parity matters, the scalar `v` already drives skip/take/count, so paging is unchanged.
